com.cloudera.labs.envelope.plan.time

Interface TimeModel

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Comparator<Row>, Component
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    LongMillisTimeModel, NanosWithSeqNumTimeModel, StringDateTimeModel, StringDatetimeTimeModel, TimestampTimeModel

    public interface TimeModel
extends Component, Comparator<Row>
    A time model class contains a set of logic for representing time on a row, for example a single long field that has milliseconds since epoch, or a single string field that has a date with no time component. A time model instance refers to specific field name(s) that the instance will operate on, for example "lastupdated". A time model instance does not belong to any particular Row object so that it can be reused across rows.

      • configureCurrentSystemTime

        void configureCurrentSystemTime(long currentSystemTimeMillis)
        Configure the current system time of the time model. This is separate to the configure method because it could be called multiple times over the lifetime of the instance.
        Parameters:
        currentSystemTimeMillis - The current system time as milliseconds since epoch.

      • setFarFutureTime

        Row setFarFutureTime(Row row)
        Set the time model instance fields to a time in the far future. At a minimum the far future should be after the year 2100, but typically the date 9999-12-31 is used.
        Parameters:
        row - The row to be set. This instance will not be modified.
        Returns:
        The row with the far future time set.

      • setPrecedingSystemTime

        Row setPrecedingSystemTime(Row row)
        Set the time model instance fields to the preceding moment of the current system time. The preceding moment is defined by the granularity of time in the time model type.
        Parameters:
        row - The row to be set. This instance will not be modified.
        Returns:
        The row with the preceding system time set.
